{"_id":"9Gao7s1QuRoRJowR","name":"Forlorn Philosopher","type":"class","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/forlorn-philosopher.webp","data":{"abilities":"<p>Small, roll 3d6&minus;2 for Strength. Stealthy, all Presence and Agility tests have their DR reduced by 2 (normal tests are DR10 instead of DR12). Roll d6 on the weapon table and d2 on the armor table. You also begin with one specialty:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Coward's Jab</li>\n<li>Filthy Fingersmith</li>\n<li>Abominable Gob Lobber</li>\n<li>Escaping Fate</li>\n<li>Excretal Stealth</li>\n<li>Dodging Death</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The first time the Scum gets better another specialty is rolled. From the second time the Scum gets better it&rsquo;s possible to reroll these two specialities or just one.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","armorTableDie":"1d2","description":"The road an unreasoning maze, every temple soaked in blood, each destination drenched in gloom; you once thought that cold analysis might tame Fate itself, now that dream of reason has decayed to shifting madness and only the cold remains","omenDie":"1d4","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d4","startingItems":"frontierscum.class-forlorn-philosopher,Ruthless Inquisition","startingPresence":"3d6+2","startingRolls":"frontierscum.rolls-forlorn-philosopher,Roots of Your Dejection,1\nfrontierscum.rolls-forlorn-philosopher,Forlorn Philosopher Items,1\nfrontierscum.tablet-of-ochre-obscurity,,Tablet of Ochre Obscurity,1","startingSilver":"1d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6-2","startingToughness":"3d6","weaponTableDie":"1d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-gutterborn-scum.gAx8MWLiZcjiWQvc"}}}
{"_id":"EgFvnowhTTc2bP1w","name":"Sash of the Stylite","type":"misc","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>The MIND controls the body! Nothing is good or bad but thinking makes it so including calories and protein. Wearing this belt means you feel no hunger and only need to drink water to regain HP when resting. Wearing it for more than d4 days causes you to collapse. It takes a day to regain its power.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"carried":true,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"G5e0J7U8cICNdE6T","name":"Ruthless Inquisition","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/forlorn-philosopher.webp","data":{"description":"<p>Ruthless Inquisition: test Presence DR 14 to tear through others&rsquo; deceptions and delusions. Enough of these LIES!</p>","rollFormula":"1d20+@abilities.presence.value","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":"Ruthless Inquisition"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-gutterborn-scum.aOwKOQge7XSi5Mma"}}}
{"_id":"Gk5tQ6DtPQDNpHcE","name":"Marked by Obscurity","type":"misc","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>An ever-shifting Tablet of Ochre Obscurity is tattooed on your flesh. Roll each morning which tablet it is. The tablet can only be used once per day but automatically succeeds.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"carried":true,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"k5Geoxqw8ejckHwL","name":"Thorns of Comprehension","type":"misc","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>When worn, thorns pierce your flesh (d2 damage) and you Perceive All (-4DR to your next test and ignore the next two attacks to hit you as you weave aside). To regain the effect you must crown yourself anew. The damage steps up by one each time (d2 to d4 to d6 etc), until after a night&rsquo;s rest.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"carried":true,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"kKFqHM9iN6l6iRhL","name":"Hegelian Owl","type":"misc","img":"modules/smoke-raven/mork%20borg/creatures/hegelian-owl.webp","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>This philosophical beast is a bitter, reluctant and hypersensitive assistant &mdash;persuaded with a DR12 Presence test. After two acts of aid it regards you with mute contempt. It can fetch small items, attack enemies and find traps. By night the owl delivers understanding of what you should have done today in dreams.</p>\n<p>@Actor[rQOrHNCsJgP8hZZd]{Hegelian Owl}</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"carried":true,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ncaCpz1x0VM2A6YP","name":"Prism of Ambiguity","type":"misc","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>An external light source and a Presence DR10 test are needed to activate the prism. Its light may shine on up to two creatures healing d6 HP. For the next hour one of them lowers all test DRs by -2. If the test is failed they suffer d4 damage and their armor or a weapon is destroyed. You can use the prism twice per day.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"carried":true,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"tvmMqVFb0PsBLlJF","name":"Flute of Tosk","type":"misc","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Once per combat, when a creature dies, you may play this bone flute&rsquo;s Echoing Fugue. This deals an &lsquo;echo&rsquo; of the fatal damage to a random enemy in the vicinity.&nbsp;</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"carried":true,"price":0,"quantity":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{}}
